Workplace Transport Risk Assessment

Work activities involving vehicles (including visiting vehicles) shall be identified over a reasonable period (e.g. over the course of a week). Activities may include:

Arrival and departure;

Travel within the workplace;

Loading, unloading and securing loads;

Coupling and uncoupling; and

Vehicle maintenance work.



The risks associated with these activities shall be identified, including but not limited to:

Struck by a moving vehicle;

Fall from a vehicle (e.g., while getting in or out, or during loading);

Struck by object falling from vehicle;

Tipping of vehicle.
